# dynamodb-toolkit — AI Agent Rules

## Project identity

`dynamodb-toolkit` is a zero-runtime-dependency, opinionated, **ESM-only** micro-library for AWS DynamoDB. v3 builds on the AWS JS SDK v3 (`@aws-sdk/client-dynamodb` + `@aws-sdk/lib-dynamodb`). It ships an `Adapter` class, expression builders, batch + transaction chunking, mass operations, and a framework-agnostic REST core + `node:http` handler. The npm package is `dynamodb-toolkit`.

## Critical rules

- **ESM only.** `import`/`export`. No CommonJS, no transpiler. `"type": "module"` in `package.json`.
- **`.js` + hand-written `.d.ts` sidecars** — not true TypeScript. Both files live next to each other.
- **Zero runtime dependencies.** Anything in `package.json` `dependencies` is wrong. The SDK is a `peerDependencies` entry.
- **No `node:*` runtime imports in `src/`.** Type-only `import type {…} from 'node:http'` in `.d.ts` is fine; runtime code stays portable across Node, Bun, and Deno.
- **No `any` in `.d.ts`.** Use proper shapes or `unknown`.
- **Do not import from `aws-sdk` (v2) anywhere.** v3 is exclusively `@aws-sdk/*`.
- **Do not modify `wiki/`** unless explicitly asked — it's a separate git submodule.
- **Do not add or remove comments** unless explicitly asked.
- **Do not introduce a build step, transpiler, or bundler.** The package ships source as-is.

## Code style

- Prettier: see `.prettierrc`. Run `npm run lint:fix` before commits.
- 2-space indentation (see `.editorconfig`).
- Arrow functions + FP style preferred; classes only when long-lived state earns one (`Adapter`, `Raw`, `TransactionLimitExceededError`).
- `async`/`await` for I/O; promises returned, no callbacks.
- Default to no comments. Add a one-line comment only when the WHY is non-obvious.

## Architecture quick reference

- `src/index.js` re-exports `Adapter`, `Raw`, `raw`, `TransactionLimitExceededError`, and SDK type names. Consumers do `import {Adapter} from 'dynamodb-toolkit'`.
- The Adapter is a composition root over `expressions/`, `batch/`, `mass/`, `paths/`. Each is independently importable via the `exports` map.
- `Raw<T>` is the only bypass marker (the v2 `Raw` / `DbRaw` pair collapsed). `raw(item)` wraps; on writes it skips `prepare` + `validateItem`; on reads with `{reviveItems: false}` results come back wrapped.
- Write paths funnel through `make*()` builders that return `{action, params}` discriminators. CRUD methods consult `hooks.checkConsistency()` and may upgrade single ops to `transactWriteItems` when extra checks exist. `TRANSACTION_LIMIT` is 100.
- `indirectIndices` marks GSIs that project keys only — reads against those automatically do a second-hop `BatchGetItem` via `readOrderedListByKeys`.
- The REST surface splits into `dynamodb-toolkit/rest-core` (parsers/builders/policy, framework-agnostic) and `dynamodb-toolkit/handler` (`(req, res) =>` for `node:http`).

## Verification

- `npm test` — unit + mock-based integration via tape-six. No Docker required.
- `npm run test:e2e` — end-to-end against `amazon/dynamodb-local` (Docker). Bakes in `TAPE6_WORKER_START_TIMEOUT=60000` for the Docker startup.
- `npm run ts-check` — strict `tsc --noEmit` over `.d.ts`.
- `npm run js-check` — `tsc --project tsconfig.check.json` (allowJs + checkJs + noUnusedLocals/Parameters) — catches unused vars and undeclared refs in `.js`.
- `npm run lint` / `npm run lint:fix` — Prettier check / fix.

## File layout

- Entry: `src/index.js` / `src/index.d.ts`
- Adapter + hooks + transaction-upgrade: `src/adapter/`
- Expression builders: `src/expressions/`
- Batch/transaction chunking: `src/batch/`
- Mass ops + pagination: `src/mass/`
- Path helpers: `src/paths/`
- REST core: `src/rest-core/`
- HTTP handler: `src/handler/`
- Bare files: `src/raw.js`, `src/sleep.js`, `src/seq.js`, `src/random.js`
- Tests: `tests/test-*.js` (unit), `tests/e2e/test-*.js` (Docker), `tests/helpers/`, `tests/fixtures/`
- Design docs: `dev-docs/v3-survey.md`, `dev-docs/v3-design.md`, `dev-docs/v3-plan.md`
- Wiki: `wiki/` (git submodule)

## When reading the codebase

- Start with `dev-docs/v3-design.md` for the authoritative rationale.
- `src/adapter/adapter.js` is the composition root — read it before touching CRUD or mass ops.
- `src/handler/handler.js` is the standard REST route pack — see for the URL contract.
- `src/expressions/update.js` documents the patch + array-op semantics.
- The wiki at https://github.com/uhop/dynamodb-toolkit/wiki has the published API reference. The `v2.3-docs` git tag in the wiki repo preserves v2 documentation.
